From: conao3 <conao3@gmail.com>
Subject: codex/app_server: emit jsonrpc field on outgoing messages

claude-app-server (sapsaldog/claude-app-server, the Claude Code
back-end of Symphony's Codex JSON-RPC protocol) validates incoming
lines strictly against `jsonrpc === "2.0"` in `protocol.ts`. Symphony's
own `send_message` omits this field, so any non-Codex app-server
implementation that follows the JSON-RPC 2.0 spec rejects Symphony's
requests and times out at `initialize`.

Add the field on the way out so symphony can drive both `codex
app-server` and conforming third-party app-servers.

---
 lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex b/lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex
--- a/lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex
+++ b/lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex
@@ -1055,7 +1055,7 @@ defmodule SymphonyElixir.Codex.AppServer do
   defp tool_call_arguments(_params), do: %{}

   defp send_message(port, message) do
-    line = Jason.encode!(message) <> "\n"
+    line = (message |> Map.put("jsonrpc", "2.0") |> Jason.encode!()) <> "\n"
     Port.command(port, line)
   end
